column2: The kingdom of Gallia has been on a downward spiral for the last century, but no longer! The old city of Suéson has been liberated, and Dihón firmly rests in Gallic hands. It is time to push the Hun out of Gallia, once and for all.
This decision fires an event which will allow you to free or return cores to your vassals.
The Pannonian sea has long been one of the most important bodies of water, if we connect it with the Mediterranean Sea we can bring it into new relevancy.
